Classification of Machine Learning Types

1. Supervised Learning
Learning from labeled data where each input has a corresponding output.

Subtypes:

Regression: Predicting continuous values
Examples: House price prediction, temperature forecasting
Algorithms: Linear Regression, Polynomial Regression
Classification: Predicting categorical values
Examples: Email spam detection, disease diagnosis
Algorithms: Decision Trees, Random Forest, Logistic Regression, SVM

2. Unsupervised Learning
Learning patterns from unlabeled data without predefined outputs.

Subtypes:

Clustering: Grouping similar data points
Examples: Customer segmentation, gene sequencing
Algorithms: K-Means, Hierarchical Clustering, DBSCAN
Dimensionality Reduction: Reducing data features
Examples: Feature extraction, data visualization
Algorithms: PCA (Principal Component Analysis), t-SNE
Association Rules: Finding relationships between variables
Examples: Market basket analysis, recommendation systems
Algorithms: Apriori, Eclat

3. Semi-supervised Learning
Combining small amounts of labeled data with large amounts of unlabeled data.

Applications:

Speech recognition
Text classification
Medical image analysis
Algorithms: Self-training, Co-training, Generative models

4. Reinforcement Learning
Learning through interactions with an environment using rewards and penalties.

Key Concepts:

Agent, Environment, State, Action, Reward
Goal: Maximize cumulative reward
Applications:

Game playing (Chess, Go)
Robotics and autonomous systems
Recommendation engines
Algorithms: Q-Learning, Deep Q-Networks (DQN), Policy Gradient

5. Transfer Learning
Using knowledge from one task to improve performance on another task.

Applications:

Image recognition (pre-trained models)
Natural Language Processing
Domain adaptation
